Vice President Mike Pence delivered a speech at the annual meeting of the Ohio Oil and Gas Association in Columbus, Ohio. He praised the oil and gas industry for fostering American energy and highlighted the achievements of the Trump administration in promoting American energy production and economic growth. Pence emphasized the importance of border security and called on Congress to support President Trump's national emergency declaration. He also warned against the dangers of socialism and urged attendees to continue growing their businesses and spreading the message of conservative principles. Pence expressed confidence in the future of Ohio and the United States.